args:
The prince and his friends tumble into a giant
underground space and find a mass of dragons
writhing within. After Phares, Beren, and the
dragons take flight, the heroes return home and
learn that the capital is nearly unguarded,
at which point they decide to march.
Ain't sure how far underground we are,\nbut my butt sure as hell hurts from the fall.
I can't see a thing in this darkness.\nWhere ARE we?
Keep your blade at the ready, Highness.\nWe appear to be surrounded.
No wonder more kept comin' every\ntime we took one down. How in the\nhell many ARE there?!
Dozens. Hundreds. Perhaps more.\nIt is a number beyond counting.
I must apologize for the somewhat\nrough treatment you have received.
Phares! How did you manage to gather\ntogether this many void dragons?!
With the Empress's gracious assistance,\nwe captured dragons from across the land,\nthen used black mana to seize control.
Her goal and mine are one and the same:\nThe enslavement of every last dragon\nin the world entire.
If this many dragons were loosed upon\nthe world, there's no telling what would\nbecome of Alberia.
I will never let that happen.
I'll fight until my last for Alberia!
And my sword will be ever at your side.
You go to great efforts to safeguard\na thing not even worth protecting.
They're bringin' it down on top of us!
Holy snot, man... They're all flying away.
Let us be off, Beren; we must report the\nresults of this experiment to the Empress.
Farewell, little {player_name}.\nI look forward to seeing if you remain\nyourself when next we meet.
My thanks for your cooperation. Ta ta!
So invading insects squirm and wriggle\nat our Empire's borders, hmm? How very\nbothersome. ...Well? What will you do?

Dispatch them with your leave, Empress.
If those who would violate our sovereignty
are left unchecked, it could shake the
very foundations of the Empire.
You are as forthright as ever, General.\nYet I thought you knew I had no interest\nin the fate of this nation.
Even so, there are things required of you,\nhaving named yourself ruler of it.
Very well. Use the forces under your\ncommand and rain death upon the fools\nwho dare to invade this land.
Understood. I will prepare to march\nand depart with all haste.
With this, all who carry the dragonblood\nwill be absent from the capital.
The only forces remaining are the\nCapital Guarda truly fortuitous\nset of circumstances!
Yet what will you do with these favorable\nconditions, my dear elder brother?
Heh. I shall have to keep you suitably\nentertained in the palace. For courtesy's\nsake, of course. Ha ha! Aaaah ha ha ha!
Your Highness, your brother Leonidas\nhas departed the Halidom and returned\nto Valkaheim.
Though he is recovering from his injuries,\nit will likely be some time before he is\nable to venture forth again.
Additionally, Princess Chelle has stationed\nherself in Rovetelle for the nonce.
The princess also sent a messenger\nto the Halidom a short while ago.
Prince Valyx has left the capital\nand is on the march north.
Why would he be doing that...?
If I may, Your Highness, we find ourselves\npresented with a golden opportunity.
With Leonidas and Emile's armies lost\nand Chelle and Valyx's absent, the capital\nfinds itself woefully short of forces.
All that remain are Harle's Capital Guard\nand Phares. And after them...Morsayati.
Make ready to march for the capital.\nWe leave at once.
By your leave, I will be at your side\nfor I would follow you to the ends\nof the very world itself.
I'll be counting on you, Leif.
Hold on, Zethia. I'm going to defeat\nMorsayati and save you. ...I swear it.
